02:03:30,120 --> 02:03:36,040
is our own hubris and in the sense of isolation that we have historically always felt.

968
02:03:36,040 --> 02:03:39,480
But why wasn't it enough that it had happened abroad? They were still U.S. lives.

969
02:03:40,120 --> 02:03:45,560
Yes, they were. And they should have been counted more dearly, but they weren't. And I, you know,

970
02:03:46,520 --> 02:03:51,400
it's similar with our wars, don't you think? You know, I mean, we have wars, people die.

971
02:03:51,880 --> 02:03:57,480
Sometimes there is a tribute to them in the paper and you see their pictures, but not often.

972
02:03:57,480 --> 02:04:03,320
And so it's the cost of doing business. You know, we are not as...

973
02:04:06,360 --> 02:04:14,280
There's a gap between our role in the world and the people we think we are. And I think this was

974
02:04:14,280 --> 02:04:22,760
especially true before 9-11. The reason Bin Laden attacked us is, you know, he felt surrounded.

975
02:04:23,480 --> 02:04:31,160
He felt America was encircling the Islamic world and they were under threat. And why would we do

976
02:04:31,160 --> 02:04:38,840
that? Well, obviously our goal would be to destroy Islam. And then there was at the same time, this

977
02:04:39,640 --> 02:04:47,960
mandate he had in his mind that Islam has to rise again once it was the superpower. It went all the

978
02:04:47,960 --> 02:04:59,400
way into middle Europe and to southern China. It was an expansionist power and that it should

979
02:04:59,400 --> 02:05:05,480
resume that role. So there was the sense of being threatened by the superpower and the feeling that

980
02:05:05,480 --> 02:05:13,720
Islam should replace it. And that was, I think, the dynamic that was driving him. And nobody in...

981
02:05:15,560 --> 02:05:21,800
I can't say nobody in America, but very few people in America would have imagined that such

982
02:05:22,920 --> 02:05:30,600
preposterous dreams would motivate somebody like Bin Laden and actually be able to put into effect

983
02:05:30,600 --> 02:05:39,800
an attack on this nation that was seemingly invulnerable, that was so distant, how could you

984
02:05:39,800 --> 02:05:47,400
even reach it? And how could you touch it in a way that would make it suffer? Yes, Bin Laden wanted

985
02:05:47,400 --> 02:05:55,720
America to suffer. And he also wanted to humiliate America because I think he understood the power

986
02:05:55,800 --> 02:06:04,920
of humiliation. Now, going back to O'Neill and Scheuer, they agreed on one thing, which was

987
02:06:04,920 --> 02:06:13,240
Osama Bin Laden was a really bad actor and needed to be taken seriously. In fact, you could argue

988
02:06:13,240 --> 02:06:19,400
that no two people believed it more than these two. I think that's fair. One who headed the CIA's

989
02:06:20,360 --> 02:06:26,120
Alak station, which was in charge of anti-terrorism, and the other I-49, which was the FBI's response

990
02:06:26,120 --> 02:06:32,840
to that. But beyond that, they didn't see anything eye to eye. Fundamentally, O'Neill believed that

991
02:06:32,840 --> 02:06:37,800
Bin Laden and other operatives of Al Qaeda should be brought to justice in the court of law in the

992
02:06:37,800 --> 02:06:46,520
United States. Scheuer and colleagues believed these people should be assassinated. An attempt

993
02:06:46,760 --> 02:06:53,960
was made to assassinate Bin Laden in 1998 after the bombing in Kenya. It was a bit of a debacle.

994
02:06:53,960 --> 02:06:59,480
It didn't amount to anything. Why is that? Was it failed intelligence? Well,

995
02:07:00,920 --> 02:07:06,360
one thing, here's the thinking that was going on inside at that time, Clinton White House.

996
02:07:07,560 --> 02:07:12,760
They hit us twice. Well, we should hit them back twice. This is the kind of thing you do

997
02:07:12,760 --> 02:07:22,600
with nation states, parallel responses. We'll bomb training camps in Afghanistan, and we'll hit

998
02:07:22,600 --> 02:07:29,240
this factory in Khartoum that we think is manufacturing poison chemicals for Al Qaeda.

999
02:07:29,240 --> 02:07:35,640
Actually, it was making veterinary medicines, and it was one of the main factories in the whole

1000
02:07:35,640 --> 02:07:41,640
country, a very poor country. We killed a night watchman. It just had nothing to do with any of it.

1001
02:07:43,000 --> 02:07:48,920
We bombed the camps in Afghanistan. Fingers crossed Bin Laden would be there. Well, he wasn't.

1002
02:07:49,880 --> 02:07:55,480
He was on the road to go there and then changed his mind, and they went somewhere else. So,

1003
02:07:55,480 --> 02:08:02,280
it might have happened, but it didn't. But the point was, look what we can do. You hit us,

1004
02:08:02,280 --> 02:08:10,840
we'll hit you back. Well, that's exactly what Bin Laden wanted. The failure of imagination that

1005
02:08:10,840 --> 02:08:16,360
you referenced, there was a failure of imagination, but it was coupled with

1006
02:08:20,040 --> 02:08:28,280
prejudicial ideas about who we're dealing with and a tremendous absence of knowledge about the

1007
02:08:28,280 --> 02:08:34,040
cultures that our adversaries came from. So, we just didn't understand, and we couldn't understand

1008
02:08:34,040 --> 02:08:39,000
their language. We didn't know what was going on. And so, yeah, it is not a surprise that our

1009
02:08:39,000 --> 02:08:46,760
imaginations didn't rise to the task because we didn't know who we're dealing with, and we could

1010
02:08:46,760 --> 02:08:51,560
not figure them out, nor did we really spend very much time worrying about it. Let's just deal with

1011
02:08:51,560 --> 02:08:58,440
them as if it was Russia that did this, and we'll strike them back proportionally. And

1012
02:09:01,560 --> 02:09:08,040
Clinton did have the idea, he spoke to one of his military commanders about sending in ninjas,

1013
02:09:09,640 --> 02:09:15,400
dropped, rappelled down from Cobra helicopters, and that sure surprised Bin Laden. And

1014
02:09:17,160 --> 02:09:21,720
on balance, it wasn't a bad idea. That was probably the right thing to do, go directly in there.

1015
02:09:23,560 --> 02:09:31,960
But we were still in the remote control phase of our imperial rule. And

1016
02:09:32,840 --> 02:09:39,000
I think that that's partly why we didn't take the embassy bombings seriously.

1017
02:09:40,280 --> 02:09:48,840
That's not the way we do things. We send drones over, or we send F-16s, or we send bombers over,

1018
02:09:48,840 --> 02:09:54,680
and we do it remotely, and we don't dirty our hands, we don't bloody our hands.

1019
02:09:55,480 --> 02:10:02,840
And so I think people just thought it would be a nuisance, and that we would take care of it.

1020
02:10:04,440 --> 02:10:12,040
So as the coal, as the planning for the coal bombing is underway, the planning for 9-11 is

