02:19:13,800 --> 02:19:19,160
but we might get bin Laden. Well, that was the kind of thinking that Michael Shurer was capable of.

1092
02:19:19,160 --> 02:19:23,880
Yeah, which again, the UAE is an ally. I mean, it would be hard to fathom that.

1093
02:19:23,880 --> 02:19:29,320
Yeah. And we were just at that moment selling them a whole fleet of F-16s. So there was a

1094
02:19:29,320 --> 02:19:36,200
financial investment in not doing that as well in addition to the absurdity of the scene. But

1095
02:19:36,200 --> 02:19:42,200
that's the kind of thing that Shurer would propose. So who took over Alex station when Shurer was

1096
02:19:42,840 --> 02:19:47,560
terminated? The woman that took over the station

1097
02:19:48,440 --> 02:20:03,400
is an FBI view, a villain, but she and Shurer later married. And so it was an office romance.

1098
02:20:03,400 --> 02:20:08,440
It was an extension of Shurer anyway. Now, one of the things that's interesting about

1099
02:20:08,440 --> 02:20:14,440
Alex station is it had a number of I-49 agents that sat within it physically. So these are

1100
02:20:14,440 --> 02:20:20,280
FBI agents that are sitting inside Alex station, but they were kind of handcuffed because they were

1101
02:20:20,280 --> 02:20:26,360
privy to the information that the CIA had, but they weren't permitted to share it with their

1102
02:20:26,360 --> 02:20:32,920
colleagues at FBI. One of the things that struck me as odd is that none of them broke rank, right?

1103
02:20:32,920 --> 02:20:39,640
Like you see in Edward Snowden, you know, a decade later, who, you know, goes completely rogue and

1104
02:20:40,280 --> 02:20:45,080
decides for right or wrong, this is his conviction. This is what he's going to do about it. This is in

1105
02:20:45,080 --> 02:20:51,640
the life. This isn't the best interest of American lives. And yet amazingly, none of the FBI agents

1106
02:20:51,640 --> 02:20:58,040
sitting inside of Alex station who presumably saw what was happening, didn't think I'm willing to

1107
02:20:58,600 --> 02:21:05,640
jeopardize my job here and maybe face criminal charges to get information because they saw the

1108
02:21:05,640 --> 02:21:12,920
wires coming in. They saw the requests repeatedly from the FBI, from Sufan saying, who are these

1109
02:21:12,920 --> 02:21:19,640
people? What happened in Malaysia? Why is money leaving to go to these people? Why is this money

1110
02:21:19,640 --> 02:21:24,440
coming to the United States? I mean, did you ever get an insight into why the FBI people inside

1111
02:21:24,440 --> 02:21:32,360
Alex station were, were, were muzzled? You know, there was a, it was more of a legal

1112
02:21:32,360 --> 02:21:39,000
conceit. They called the wall. And the idea was that information should not travel from the

1113
02:21:39,000 --> 02:21:48,280
intelligence world into the criminal one and vice versa. There was really no law. There was,

1114
02:21:48,280 --> 02:21:54,360
people thought it was a law, but there was a, it was a custom and an FBI had its own intelligence

1115
02:21:54,360 --> 02:22:02,280
division. And so it was part of the, just is like grand jury testimony. You know, it's not supposed,

1116
02:22:02,280 --> 02:22:09,000
it's supposed to be sealed, you know, it's kept, kept pure and secret. But

1117
02:22:11,640 --> 02:22:17,160
when you're faced with something like that, the only alternative, you know, is to break the law.

1118
02:22:17,160 --> 02:22:22,200
And there can be very serious consequences and it's a lonely thing to do. But that's really the

1119
02:22:22,280 --> 02:22:31,720
only thing you can do. What I can tell you is how broken those people are by what happened.

1120
02:22:35,640 --> 02:22:41,240
They knew what was going to, they knew what was underway and they lost their boss. You know,

1121
02:22:41,880 --> 02:22:49,640
John O'Neill died as a consequence of their reticence to say anything. I'm not holding them

1122
02:22:49,640 --> 02:22:58,120
responsible for 9-11, but I do hold the CIA responsible for it. If they had been transparent

1123
02:22:58,120 --> 02:23:08,040
with the FBI, if they had said, we have these Aikaida members in America, the FBI had the authority,

1124
02:23:08,040 --> 02:23:13,080
they had the warrant, they had everything. They could follow them. They could tape them. They could,

1125
02:23:13,080 --> 02:23:19,960
you know, clone their computers and they could arrest them. There were all these things that

1126
02:23:19,960 --> 02:23:31,960
they could do, but they were kept in the dark. And of course, the question is why? And I've asked,

1127
02:23:33,000 --> 02:23:36,040
you know, I- How many people in the CIA were you able to interview?

1128
02:23:36,280 --> 02:23:49,320
Uh, they were actually working in the CIA. There was a moment where I think it's

